# Page Object Conventions

## Inheritance

All page objects **must** extend `BasePage` from `src/page-objects/00-shared/base.page.ts`.

```typescript
import { BasePage } from "../00-shared/base.page";

export class MyNewPage extends BasePage {
  // ...
}
```

## BasePage Provides

These methods are inherited — use them instead of raw Playwright calls:

| Method | Use For |
|---|---|
| `navigateTo(path)` | Go to a route (auto-prepends `BASE_URL`) |
| `waitForUrl(pattern, timeout)` | Wait for URL to match |
| `getCurrentUrl()` | Get current URL |
| `clickElement(locator)` | Wait + click |
| `fillInput(locator, value)` | Wait + clear + fill |
| `selectDropdownByTestId(testId, optionText)` | Open Radix Select → pick option (3 fallback strategies) |
| `getToastMessage()` | Get text from toast/sonner notification |
| `waitForLoadingToDisappear()` | Wait for `.animate-spin` to vanish |
| `waitForNetworkIdle(timeout)` | Wait for network idle |
| `isElementVisible(locator, timeout)` | Try/catch visibility check → boolean |

## Locator Strategy (Priority Order)

1. **`getByTestId("...")`** — preferred when the app has `data-testid` attributes
2. **`getByRole("...", { name: /.../ })`** — for buttons, headings, links
3. **`page.locator('...')`** — CSS selector as fallback
4. **Never use XPath** unless absolutely required

## Locator Declaration

Declare locators as **readonly class fields** (not inside methods):

```typescript
export class MyPage extends BasePage {
  // ✅ Correct – field-level, readonly
  private readonly saveBtn = this.page.getByTestId("button-save");
  readonly sectionTitle = this.page.getByRole("heading", { name: /My Section/i });

  // ❌ Wrong – locator created inside method
  async doSomething() {
    const btn = this.page.getByTestId("button-save"); // Don't do this
  }
}
```

- Use `private readonly` for locators only used internally
- Use `readonly` (public) for locators that tests assert on directly (e.g., `employeeDashboardPage.myActivitiesSection`)

## Method Patterns

| Type | Naming | Returns | Example |
|---|---|---|---|
| Navigation | `goto()`, `openXxxForm()` | `Promise<void>` | `async goto()` |
| Form fill | `fillXxx(value)` | `Promise<void>` | `async fillJobTitle(title: string)` |
| Dropdown | `selectXxx(value)` | `Promise<void>` | `async selectDepartment(dept: string)` |
| Assertion | `verifyXxx()`, `expectXxx()` | `Promise<void>` | `async verifyFormVisible()` |
| Composite | `fillFormData(data)` | `Promise<void>` | `async fillReferralForm(data: ReferralData)` |

## Interfaces

Define data interfaces in the page object file if they represent the form's input shape:

```typescript
export interface RequisitionData {
  jobTitle: string;
  department: string;
  // ...
}
```

## Barrel Export

After creating a new page object, register it in `src/page-objects/index.ts`:

```typescript
export { MyNewPage } from "./05-feature/my-new.page";
export type { MyNewData } from "./05-feature/my-new.page";
```

## Dropdown Handling

The app uses **Radix UI Select** components. Use `selectDropdownByTestId()` from BasePage which handles:
1. Clicking the trigger
2. Waiting for the portal/listbox
3. Finding the option via role, then regex, then text

For `cmdk`-based select/combobox components (like requisition/relationship selects in referrals), use the `selectFirstAvailableOption()` pattern from ReferralsPage.

## Toast / Sonner Assertions

The app uses **Sonner** for toasts. Use these locator patterns:
```typescript
// Generic toast
this.page.locator('[role="status"], [data-sonner-toast]').first();

// Specific message
this.page.locator('[role="status"], [data-sonner-toast], .sonner-toast')
  .filter({ hasText: /success|submitted/i });
```

## File Naming

```
src/page-objects/<NN>-<feature>/<feature-name>.page.ts
```
Examples: `01-login/login.page.ts`, `04-referrals/referrals.page.ts`
